---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const LAST_UPDATED = "March 15, 2026";
const DEVELOPER = "Artificial Igknorance";
const CONTACT_EMAIL = "info@artificialigknorance.com";
---

<Layout title="Terms of Use — Artificial Igknorance">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-12 px-4">

    <!-- Back link -->
    <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors mb-8 text-sm">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"/>
      </svg>
      Back to Home
    </a>

    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-400 to-cyan-300 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
      Terms of Use
    </h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-10">
      {DEVELOPER} &middot; Last updated {LAST_UPDATED}
    </p>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none space-y-8">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          By downloading, installing, or using any app published by {DEVELOPER} ("the App"), you agree to
          be bound by these Terms of Use ("Terms"). If you do not agree to these Terms, do not use the App.
          These Terms constitute a legally binding agreement between you and {DEVELOPER}.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">2. Description of Service</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          Our apps are reference and productivity tools intended for informational and educational purposes
          only. Nothing in any of our apps constitutes financial, investment, medical, legal, or professional
          advice. Always consult a qualified professional before making decisions based on information
          displayed in our apps.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">3. Subscription and In-App Purchases</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          Some apps offer optional premium subscriptions through Apple's In-App Purchase system.
          Where a subscription is offered:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2 mt-3 ml-4">
          <li>Payment is charged to your Apple ID account upon confirmation of purchase.</li>
          <li>Subscriptions automatically renew unless cancelled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.</li>
          <li>A free trial period may be offered for new subscribers. Your subscription will automatically convert to a paid subscription unless cancelled before the trial ends.</li>
          <li>You can manage and cancel subscriptions in your Apple ID Account Settings (Settings &rsaquo; Apple ID &rsaquo; Subscriptions).</li>
          <li>No refund is provided for the unused portion of a subscription period.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">4. Data Accuracy Disclaimer</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          Where our apps display financial, medical, or other data sourced from third-party providers,
          we make no warranty that the data is complete, accurate, or up-to-date. Data may be delayed
          or subject to errors. Do not make financial, health, or other important decisions based solely
          on data displayed in our apps.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">5. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          All content, design, graphics, and code in our apps are the property of {DEVELOPER} and are
          protected by applicable intellectual property laws. You may not reproduce, distribute, or create
          derivative works from any part of our apps without prior written permission.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">6. Prohibited Uses</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">You agree not to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2 mt-3 ml-4">
          <li>Use any app for any unlawful purpose.</li>
          <li>Attempt to reverse-engineer, decompile, or disassemble any app.</li>
          <li>Use automated tools to scrape or extract data from any app.</li>
          <li>Interfere with any app's operation or servers.</li>
          <li>Misrepresent your identity or affiliation.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">7. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed uppercase text-sm">
          Our apps are provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, either express
          or implied, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular
          purpose, and non-infringement. We do not warrant that any app will be uninterrupted, error-free,
          or free of viruses or other harmful components.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed uppercase text-sm">
          To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, {DEVELOPER} shall not be liable for any
          indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including loss of profits,
          data, or goodwill, arising out of or in connection with your use of any app, even if advised
          of the possibility of such damages.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">9. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. We will notify you of material changes
          by updating the "Last updated" date above. Your continued use of any app after changes are posted
          constitutes your acceptance of the revised Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">10. Governing Law</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Province of Alberta,
          Canada, without regard to conflict of law principles.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">11. Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          If you have questions about these Terms, please contact us:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 p-4 bg-white/5 rounded-xl border border-white/10">
          <p class="text-white font-semibold">{DEVELOPER}</p>
          <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`} class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors">
            {CONTACT_EMAIL}
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
